President  Nicolas Sarkozy  meets
with local leaders and executives from transport companies to
promote greater use of canals to move freight.  German Defense Minister Thomas de Maiziere visits his
French counterpart Gerard Longuet.  ALL TIMES CET  PM EARNINGS
* Burelle (BUR FP) full-year earns 5:30 p.m.
* SIIC de Paris (IMMP FP) full-year earns 5:30 p.m.  ECONOMY: Data and events today
* 9:50 a.m. PMI Services  GOVERNMENT:
* President Sarkozy speaks on river and canal transport in the
Somme 11:00 a.m.
* Foreign Minister Juppe meets Romania’s Baconschi at the Quai
d’Orsay 12:45 p.m.
* Defense Minister Gerard Longuet holds press conference with
German counterpart Thomas de Maiziere 2:30 p.m.
* Government question time 3 p.m.
* Government UMP party holds roundtable discussions on religion
and secularism 3:30 p.m.  EQUITIES:
*  Schneider Electric SA (SU)  : The electrical equipment maker
paid an undisclosed sum for Lee Technologies, an equipment
provider for data centers based in Fairfax, Virginia with sales
of about $140 million in 2010. The shares fell 0.1 percent to
123.15 euros.
*  Vivendi SA (VIV)  : The communications company’s complete
takeover of mobile-phone operator SFR will add about 600
million euros in adjusted net income in each of 2012 and 2013,
Chief Executive Officer Jean-Bernard Levy said on a conference
call. The shares gained 0.6 percent to 20.64 euros.  MARKETS:
*The CAC 40 Index fell 0.29 percent to 4042.92.
*The broader SBF 120 Index fell 0.1 percent to 3036.45.  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
